<eesti>Prokur&ouml;rile esitatavad n&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for prosecutors </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Prokur&ouml;riks v&otilde;ib nimetada teov&otilde;imelise v&auml;hemalt 21-aastase Eesti kodaniku, kellel on akadeemiline k&otilde;rgharidus &otilde;igusteaduses, kes valdab eesti keelt seadusega v&otilde;i seaduse alusel kehtestatud ulatuses, kes on k&otilde;rgete k&otilde;lbeliste omadustega ning kellel on vajalikud v&otilde;imed ja isikuomadused. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An Estonian citizen with active legal capacity who has attained at least 21 years of age, has completed an academic higher education in law, is proficient in Estonian to the extent established by or pursuant to law, is of high moral character and has the necessary abilities and personal characteristics may be appointed as a prosecutor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Prokur&ouml;riks ei v&otilde;i nimetada isikut: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The following shall not be appointed as a prosecutor: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kelle kohta on j&otilde;ustunud s&uuml;&uuml;dim&otilde;istev kohtuotsus tahtlikult toimepandud kuriteo eest; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a person in respect of whom a conviction for an intentionally committed criminal offence has entered into force; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kes on vabastatud avalikust teenistusest distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teo eest; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a person who has been released from the public service for a disciplinary offence; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kes on v&auml;lja heidetud Eesti Advokatuurist v&otilde;i tagandatud notari ametist; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a person who has been disbarred from the Estonian Bar Association or expelled from the notarial profession; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kes on l&auml;hedases suguluses (vanem, vend, &otilde;de, laps) v&otilde;i h&otilde;imluses (abikaasa, abikaasa vanem, vend, &otilde;de, laps) prokur&ouml;riga, kellele ta vahetult allub; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a person closely related by blood (parent, brother, sister, child) or by marriage (spouse, spouse's parent, brother, sister, child) to the prosecutor to whom he or she is directly subordinate; </inglise>
<eesti>5) kes oma tervise t&otilde;ttu ei saa prokur&ouml;rina t&ouml;&ouml;tada. </eesti>
<inglise>5) a person who due to his or her state of health is unable to work as a prosecutor. </inglise>
<eesti>Kahtluse korral m&auml;&auml;rab isiku tervisliku seisundi kindlaks arstlik komisjon. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of doubt, a medical committee shall determine the state of health of a person. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Maa- v&otilde;i linnaprokur&ouml;riks v&otilde;ib nimetada isiku, kes vahetult enne ametisse nimetamist on t&ouml;&ouml;tanud kohtuniku, vandeadvokaadi v&otilde;i vandeadvokaadi vanemabina, samuti &otilde;ppeteenistusest vabastatud abiprokur&ouml;ri p&auml;rast katseaja l&otilde;ppemist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A person who has been employed as a judge, sworn advocate or an assistant prosecutor immediately before appointment to office, or an assistant prosecutor released from clerkship after the end of the probationary period may be appointed as a county or city prosecutor. </inglise>
<eesti>Abiprokur&ouml;ri &otilde;ppeteenistuses oleku aeg loetakse prokur&ouml;rina t&ouml;&ouml;tamise aja hulka tingimusel, et abiprokur&ouml;r on sooritanud prokur&ouml;rieksami. </eesti>
<inglise>The clerkship period of an assistant prosecutor shall be included in the period of employment as a prosecutor on the condition that the prosecutor has passed the prosecutor's examination. </inglise>
<eesti>(06.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.30.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 53, 315) </eesti>
<inglise>(06.06.2001 entered into force 30.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 53, 315) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Maakonna v&otilde;i linna vanemprokur&ouml;riks ja riigiprokur&ouml;riks v&otilde;ib nimetada isiku, kes vahetult enne ametisse nimetamist on v&auml;hemalt kolm aastat t&ouml;&ouml;tanud prokur&ouml;rina. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A person who has been employed as a prosecutor for at least three years immediately before appointment to office may be appointed as a senior county or city prosecutor or public prosecutor. </inglise>
<eesti>Abiprokur&ouml;rina &otilde;ppeteenistuses v&otilde;i katseajal olemise aega ei arvata prokur&ouml;rina t&ouml;&ouml;tamise aja hulka. </eesti>
<inglise>The clerkship period or probationary period of an assistant prosecutor shall not be included in the period of employment as a prosecutor. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Riigi peaprokur&ouml;riks v&otilde;ib nimetada isiku, kes vahetult enne ametisse nimetamist on v&auml;hemalt kolm aastat t&ouml;&ouml;tanud riigiprokur&ouml;rina v&otilde;i maakonna v&otilde;i linna vanemprokur&ouml;rina. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A person who has been employed as a public prosecutor or senior county or city prosecutor for at least three years immediately before appointment to office may be appointed as the Chief Public Prosecutor. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Prokur&ouml;riteenistusse kandideeriva isiku tausta kontrollimine </eesti>
<inglise>Scrutiny of background of persons applying for prosecutor's service </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Prokur&ouml;riteenistusse kandideeriv isik esitab prokur&ouml;ride konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjonile: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person who applies for candidate's service shall submit the following to the competition and evaluation committee: </inglise>
<eesti>1) isikuandmete ankeedi; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the form concerning personal data; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ametiisikule etten&auml;htud majanduslike huvide deklaratsiooni kandideerimisele eelneva kuu esimese kuup&auml;eva seisuga. </eesti>
<inglise>2) declaration of economic interests prescribed for officials as on the first day of the month preceding application. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Isikuandmete ankeedis m&auml;rgib kandideeriv isik ka oma sugulaste ja h&otilde;imlaste (vanemad, &otilde;de, vend, lapsed, abikaasa, endine abikaasa), samuti alalise elukaaslase ees- ja perekonnanime, isikukoodi (isikukoodi puudumisel s&uuml;nniaeg ja -koht) ja kontaktandmed. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the form concerning personal data, the applicant shall also indicate the given names, surnames, personal identification codes (in the absence of identification code, the date and place of birth) and details of the applicant's relatives and relatives by marriage (parents, sisters, brothers, children, spouse, former spouse). </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Prokur&ouml;riteenistusse kandideeriva isiku ankeedi vormi kinnitab justiitsminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The form used to apply for prosecutor's service shall be approved by the Minister of Justice. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Prokur&ouml;riteenistusse kandideeriva isiku ankeedis ja majanduslike huvide deklaratsioonis esitatud andmete &otilde;igsuse kontrollimiseks on riigi peaprokur&ouml;ril, samuti tema poolt volitatud prokuratuuriametnikel &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In order to verify the data presented in the form used to apply for prosecutor's service and the declaration of economic interests, the Chief Public Prosecutor and officials of the Prosecutor's Office authorised by the Chief Public Prosecutor have the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) p&ouml;&ouml;rduda riigi ja kohaliku omavalitsuse asutuste ja ametiisikute, samuti f&uuml;&uuml;siliste ja juriidiliste isikute poole j&auml;relep&auml;rimistega prokur&ouml;riteenistusse kandideeriva isiku isikuandmete kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>1) address local government agencies, officials of local governments, legal persons and natural persons by inquiry concerning the personal data of a person applying for prosecutor's service; </inglise>
<eesti>2) vestelda isikuandmete ankeedis m&auml;rgitud isiku, samuti t&ouml;&ouml;andja ja &otilde;ppeasutuse esindajate ning teiste isikutega, et selgitada v&auml;lja kandidaadi k&otilde;lbelisi ja teisi isikuomadusi ning vajaduse korral ja k&uuml;sitletava isiku n&otilde;usolekul v&otilde;tta temalt kirjalik seletus; </eesti>
<inglise>2) interview the person indicated in the form concerning personal data, and with employers, representatives of educational institutions and other persons in order to ascertain the moral character and other personal characteristics of the person and if necessary, obtain a written explanation from the interviewed person with his or her permission; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kontrollida, kas k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud isikud on kriminaalmenetluses kahtlustatavad, s&uuml;&uuml;distatavad v&otilde;i kohtualused. </eesti>
<inglise>3) ascertain whether the persons specified in subsection (2) of this section participate in a criminal proceeding as a suspect, the accused or the accused at trial. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esolevas paragrahvis nimetatud j&auml;relep&auml;rimise saanud asutus v&otilde;i isik vastab j&auml;relep&auml;rimisele viivitamatult. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An agency or person who receives the inquiry specified in this section shall immediately answer the inquiry. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Prokur&ouml;ride konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon teavitab prokur&ouml;riteenistusse kandideerivat isikut kohe tema suhtes l&auml;biviidud taustakontrollist ja v&otilde;imaldab tal tutvuda kontrolli k&auml;igus kogutud materjalidega. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The prosecutors' competition and evaluation committee shall immediately inform a person applying for prosecutor's service of the scrutiny conducted with regard to his or her background and enable to examine the materials gathered in the process of the checks. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Kui prokur&ouml;riteenistusse kandideeriv isik esitas prokur&ouml;ride konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjonile tahtlikult valeandmeid v&otilde;i varjas olulist informatsiooni, arvatakse kandidaat konkursilt v&auml;lja prokur&ouml;ride konkursi ja atesteerimiskomisjoni otsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) If a person intentionally presents incorrect data to the prosecutors' competition and evaluation committee or conceals material information is excluded from the competition by resolution of the prosecutors' competition and evaluation committee. </inglise>
<eesti>(06.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.30.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 53, 315) </eesti>
<inglise>(06.06.2001 entered into force 30.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 53, 315) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Prokur&ouml;ri ametisse nimetamine </eesti>
<inglise>Appointment of prosecutors to office </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigi peaprokur&ouml;ri nimetab ametisse Vabariigi Valitsus justiitsministri ettepanekul, kuulanud &auml;ra Riigikogu &otilde;iguskomisjoni arvamuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Government of the Republic shall appoint the Chief Public Prosecutor to office on the proposal of the Minister of Justice after considering the opinion of the Legal Affairs Committee of the Riigikogu (2). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maakonna ja linna vanemprokur&ouml;ri nimetab ametisse justiitsminister riigi peaprokur&ouml;ri ettepanekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Justice shall appoint senior county and city prosecutors to office on the proposal of the Chief Public Prosecutor. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Riigiprokur&ouml;ri, maa- ja linnaprokur&ouml;ri ning abiprokur&ouml;ri nimetab ametisse justiitsminister prokur&ouml;ride konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni ettepanekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Minister of Justice shall appoint public prosecutors, county and city prosecutors and assistant prosecutors to office on the proposal of the prosecutors' competition and evaluation committee. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Riigi peaprokur&ouml;riks ning maakonna ja linna vanemprokur&ouml;riks v&otilde;ib ametisse nimetada isiku, kes on selleks andnud kirjaliku n&otilde;usoleku. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A person may be appointed as the Chief Public Prosecutor or a senior county or city prosecutor if he or she gives written consent for such appointment. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Isikut ei nimetata prokur&ouml;ri ametisse, kui ta ei vasta prokur&ouml;rile esitatavatele n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A person shall not be appointed as a prosecutor if he or she does not meet the requirements for prosecutors. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametisse nimetamata j&auml;tmise otsust tuleb p&otilde;hjendada. </eesti>
<inglise>A decision not to appoint a person as a prosecutor shall be justified. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Prokur&ouml;ri ametiaeg </eesti>
<inglise>Prosecutors' term of office </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigi peaprokur&ouml;r nimetatakse ametisse viieks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Chief Public Prosecutor shall be appointed to office for a term of five years. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maakonna ja linna vanemprokur&ouml;r nimetatakse ametisse viieks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Senior county or city prosecutors shall be appointed to office for a term of five years. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Riigiprokur&ouml;r, maa- ja linnaprokur&ouml;r ning abiprokur&ouml;r nimetatakse ametisse m&auml;&auml;ramata ajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Public prosecutors, county and city prosecutors and assistant prosecutors shall be appointed to office for an unspecified term. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalik konkurss </eesti>
<inglise>Public competition </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigiprokur&ouml;r, maa- ja linnaprokur&ouml;r ning abiprokur&ouml;r nimetatakse ametisse avaliku konkursi alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Public prosecutors, county and city prosecutors and assistant prosecutors shall be appointed to office on the basis of a public competition. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Avaliku konkursi prokur&ouml;ri vabale ametikohale kuulutab Riigi Teataja Lisas v&auml;lja justiitsminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Justice shall announce a public competition for a vacant position of prosecutor in the Riigi Teataja Lisa (3). </inglise>
<eesti>Kandidaatidele tuleb avalduse esitamiseks anda aega v&auml;hemalt kaks n&auml;dalat teadaande avaldamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>Applicants shall be given at least two weeks after the date of publication of the notice for submission of their applications. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Riigi peaprokur&ouml;r ning maakonna ja linna vanemprokur&ouml;r nimetatakse ametisse avaliku konkursita. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Chief Public Prosecutor and senior county and city prosecutors shall be appointed to office without a public competition. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalikul konkursil osalejate hindamine </eesti>
<inglise>Assessment of participants in public competition </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kandidaadi sobivust ametikohale hindab prokur&ouml;ride konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The prosecutors' competition and evaluation committee shall assess the suitability of an applicant for a position. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Prokur&ouml;ri kandideerimisel vabale ametikohale esitab prokur&ouml;r, kellele kandidaat vahetult allub, prokur&ouml;ride konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjonile kandidaadi kohta p&otilde;histatud arvamuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a prosecutor applies for a vacant position, the prosecutor to whom the applicant is directly subordinate shall present a reasoned opinion on the applicant to the prosecutors' competition and evaluation committee. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>Abiprokur&ouml;ri &otilde;ppeteenistus ja katseaeg </eesti>
<inglise>Clerkship and probationary period of assistant prosecutors </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Abiprokur&ouml;ri ametikohale nimetatud isik l&auml;bib &otilde;ppeteenistuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Persons appointed as assistant prosecutors shall undergo a clerkship. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;ppeteenistus kestab kaks aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>The duration of a clerkship shall be two years. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;ppeteenistuse ajal omandab abiprokur&ouml;r maakonna v&otilde;i linna vanemprokur&ouml;ri v&otilde;i maa- v&otilde;i linnaprokur&ouml;ri juhendamisel prokur&ouml;ri t&ouml;&ouml;ks vajalikud teoreetilised teadmised ja kutseoskused. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) During a clerkship, an assistant prosecutor shall acquire the theoretical knowledge and professional skills necessary for a prosecutor under the supervision of a senior county or city prosecutor, or county or city prosecutor. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Justiitsminister vabastab &otilde;ppeteenistusest isiku, kes on varem l&auml;binud &otilde;ppeteenistuse ja sooritanud prokur&ouml;rieksami, ning v&otilde;ib vabastada &otilde;ppeteenistusest isiku, kes on v&auml;hemalt kaks aastat t&ouml;&ouml;tanud prokur&ouml;ri, kohtuniku v&otilde;i vandeadvokaadina. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Minister of Justice shall exempt from a clerkship a person who has undergone a clerkship earlier and passed the prosecutor's examination, and may exempt from a clerkship a person who has been employed as a prosecutor, judge or sworn advocate for at least two years. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) &Otilde;ppeteenistusest vabastatud abiprokur&ouml;r nimetatakse ametisse kuuekuulise katseajaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An assistant prosecutor exempted from a clerkship shall be appointed to office with a probationary period of six months. </inglise>
<eesti>Katseajal kontrollitakse abiprokur&ouml;ri kutseoskuste, v&otilde;imete ja isikuomaduste vastavust prokur&ouml;rile esitatavatele n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>During a probationary period, the compliance of the professional skills, abilities and personal characteristics of an assistant prosecutor with the requirements for prosecutors shall be assessed. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Katseaja tulemust hindab prokur&ouml;ride konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon, kuulates &auml;ra abiprokur&ouml;ri juhendava prokur&ouml;ri arvamuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The prosecutors' competition and evaluation committee shall assess the results of the probationary period of an assistant prosecutor after considering the opinion of the prosecutor supervising the assistant prosecutor. </inglise>
<eesti>Konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon teeb justiitsministrile ettepaneku katseaeg l&otilde;petada v&otilde;i vabastada abiprokur&ouml;r teenistusest katseaja ebarahuldava tulemuse t&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise>The prosecutors' competition and evaluation committee shall make a proposal to the Minister of Justice to terminate the probationary period or release the assistant prosecutor from service due to unsatisfactory completion of the probationary period. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Justiitsminister v&otilde;ib abiprokur&ouml;ri &otilde;ppeteenistuse kestust l&uuml;hendada, kuid mitte rohkem kui &uuml;he aasta v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The Minister of Justice may shorten the duration of the clerkship of an assistant prosecutor, but for not more than one year. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Prokur&ouml;rieksam </eesti>
<inglise>Prosecutor's examination </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;ppeteenistuses olevad abiprokur&ouml;rid teevad prokur&ouml;rieksami. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Assistant prosecutors who are in clerkship shall take a prosecutor's examination. </inglise>
<eesti>Prokur&ouml;rieksam toimub mitte varem kui kaks kuud enne &otilde;ppeteenistuse l&otilde;ppemist. </eesti>
<inglise>A prosecutor's examination shall be held not earlier than two months before the termination of a clerkship. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Prokur&ouml;rieksamil kontrollitakse abiprokur&ouml;ri teoreetilisi teadmisi ja situatsioon&uuml;lesannete lahendamise oskust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An assistant prosecutor's theoretical knowledge and skill in solving practical problems shall be assessed during the prosecutor's examination. </inglise>
<eesti>Eksami tegemise n&otilde;uded ja korra kehtestab justiitsminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The Minister of Justice shall establish the requirements and procedure for taking the examination. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Prokur&ouml;rieksami tulemustele antakse hinnang "sooritatud" v&otilde;i "sooritamata". </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The results of the prosecutor's examination shall be assessed as "pass" or "fail". </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui abiprokur&ouml;r eksamit ei soorita, teeb prokur&ouml;ride konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon justiitsministrile ettepaneku abiprokur&ouml;ri teenistusest vabastamiseks v&otilde;i &otilde;ppeteenistuse pikendamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If an assistant prosecutor does not pass the examination, the prosecutors' competition and evaluation committee shall propose that the Minister of Justice release the assistant prosecutor from service or extend his or her clerkship. </inglise>
<eesti>Justiitsminister v&otilde;ib &otilde;ppeteenistust pikendada kuni kuue kuu v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise>The Minister of Justice may extend a clerkship by up to six months. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui &otilde;ppeteenistust on pikendatud, toimub korduseksam mitte varem kui kaks kuud enne pikendatud &otilde;ppeteenistuse l&otilde;ppemist. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If a clerkship is extended, the re-examination shall take place not earlier than two months before the termination of the extended clerkship. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kui abiprokur&ouml;r korduseksamit ei soorita, vabastab justiitsminister abiprokur&ouml;ri teenistusest. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) If an assistant prosecutor does not pass a re-examination, the Minister of Justice shall release the assistant prosecutor from service. </inglise>
<eesti>3. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 3 </inglise>
<eesti>Ametih&uuml;ved ja s&otilde;ltumatuse tagatised </eesti>
<inglise>Benefits Related to Office and Guarantees of Independence </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametipalk </eesti>
<inglise>Salary </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Prokur&ouml;ri ametipalk on riigiteenistujate palgaastmestiku k&otilde;rgeima astme palgam&auml;&auml;ra ja k&auml;esoleva seadusega m&auml;&auml;ratud kordaja korrutis. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The salary of a prosecutor shall be the salary rate at the highest level of the salary scale for state public servants multiplied by a coefficient specified in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigi peaprokur&ouml;ri ametipalga kordaja on 1,5. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The coefficient of the salary of the Chief Public Prosecutor is 1.5. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Riigiprokuratuuri osakonda juhtiva prokur&ouml;ri ametipalga kordaja on 1,3. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The coefficient of the salary of a prosecutor who directs a department of the Public Prosecutor's Office is 1.3. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Riigiprokur&ouml;ri ning maakonna ja linna vanemprokur&ouml;ri ametipalga kordaja on 1,2. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The coefficient of the salary of a public prosecutor or senior county or city prosecutor is 1.2. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Maa- v&otilde;i linnaprokuratuuri osakonda juhtiva prokur&ouml;ri ametipalga kordaja on 1,1. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The coefficient of the salary of a prosecutor who directs a department of a county or city prosecutor's office is 1.1. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Maa- ja linnaprokur&ouml;ri ametipalga kordaja on 1,0. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The coefficient of the salary of a county or city prosecutor is 1.0. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Abiprokur&ouml;ri ametipalga kordaja on 0,7, &otilde;ppeteenistuse kestel aga 0,5. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The coefficient of the salary of an assistant prosecutor is 0.7, or 0.5 during a clerkship. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Lisatasu juhendamise eest </eesti>
<inglise>Additional remuneration for supervision </inglise>
<eesti>Abiprokur&ouml;ri juhendavale prokur&ouml;rile makstakse juhendamistasu, mille suurus on 5 protsenti juhendava prokur&ouml;ri ametipalgast iga juhendatava. kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>A prosecutor supervising an assistant prosecutor shall receive remuneration for supervision equal to 5 per cent of the salary of the supervising prosecutor for each supervised person. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 95, 839) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 95, 839) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Varalise kahju h&uuml;vitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Compensation for proprietary damage </inglise>
<eesti>Prokur&ouml;rile v&otilde;i tema perekonnaliikmele seoses prokur&ouml;ri teenistus&uuml;lesande t&auml;itmisega tekitatud varalise kahju h&uuml;vitab riik. </eesti>
<inglise>The state shall compensate a prosecutor and his or her family members for any proprietary damage which they suffer during the performance of the duties of the prosecutor. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>Prokur&ouml;ri vanaduspension </eesti>
<inglise>Prosecutor's old-age pension </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Prokur&ouml;ril, kes on prokur&ouml;rina t&ouml;&ouml;tanud v&auml;hemalt 25 aastat, on pensioniea saabumisel &otilde;igus prokur&ouml;ri vanaduspensionile. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A prosecutor who has been employed as a prosecutor for at least twenty-five years has the right to receive a prosecutor's old-age pension when he or she attains the pensionable age. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;igus prokur&ouml;ri vanaduspensionile on ka isikul, kes on prokur&ouml;rina t&ouml;&ouml;tanud v&auml;hemalt 15 aastat ja sellele eelnevalt kohtunikuna v&auml;hemalt 10 aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person who has been employed as a prosecutor for at least fifteen years and as a judge for at least ten years prior thereto also has the right to receive a prosecutor's old-age pension. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Prokur&ouml;ri vanaduspensioni suurus on 65 protsenti tema viimasest ametipalgast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The amount of a prosecutor's old-age pension is 65 per cent of the prosecutor's last salary. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui muutub selle prokur&ouml;ri ametipalk, kellena prokur&ouml;ri vanaduspensioni saav isik t&ouml;&ouml;tas, arvutatakse prokur&ouml;ri vanaduspension &uuml;mber. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If the salary of a prosecutor in the position in which the person who receives a prosecutor's old-age pension was employed is changed, the prosecutor's old-age pension shall be recalculated. </inglise>
<eesti>Sel juhul makstakse pensioni muutunud suuruses, alates j&auml;rgneva kuu esimesest kuup&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case, the pension shall be paid in the altered amount as of the first day of the following month. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Prokur&ouml;ri vanaduspensioni see osa, mis &uuml;letab &uuml;ldise vanaduspensioni, makstakse riigieelarvest. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The portion of a prosecutor's old-age pension which exceeds the general old-age pension shall be paid from the state budget. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>Prokur&ouml;ri invaliidsuspension </eesti>
<inglise>Prosecutor's disability pension </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Prokur&ouml;ri invaliidsuspensionile on &otilde;igus isikul, kes on invaliidistunud prokur&ouml;rina t&ouml;&ouml;tamise ajal ja kellel on v&auml;hemalt 15-aastane prokur&ouml;ristaa&zcaron;. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person who becomes disabled during his or her employment as a prosecutor and whose length of service as a prosecutor is at least fifteen years has the right to receive a prosecutor's disability pension. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui prokur&ouml;r on invaliidistunud seoses teenistus&uuml;lesande t&auml;itmisega tema suhtes toimepandud r&uuml;nde v&otilde;i prokur&ouml;ri poolt kuriteo t&otilde;kestamise tagaj&auml;rjel, on tal &otilde;igus invaliidsuspensionile staa&zcaron;ist s&otilde;ltumata. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a prosecutor becomes disabled due to the performance of his or her duties as a result of an attack made against him or her or as a result of the prevention of a criminal offence by the prosecutor, he or she has the right to receive a disability pension regardless of his or her length of service. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Prokur&ouml;ri I invaliidsusgrupi pension on 65 protsenti, II invaliidsusgrupi pension 50 protsenti ja III invaliidsusgrupi pension 30 protsenti prokur&ouml;ri viimasest ametipalgast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The amount of a prosecutor's pension for a category I disabled person is 65 per cent, the pension for a category II disabled person is 50 per cent and the pension for a category III disabled person is 30 per cent of the prosecutor's last salary. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui muutub invaliidsusgrupp v&otilde;i selle prokur&ouml;ri ametipalk, kellena prokur&ouml;ri invaliidsuspensioni saav isik vahetult enne invaliidistumist t&ouml;&ouml;tas, arvutatakse prokur&ouml;ri invaliidsuspension &uuml;mber. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If the category of a disabled person or the salary of a prosecutor in the position in which the person who receives a prosecutor's disability pension was employed immediately before becoming disabled is changed, the prosecutor's disability pension shall be recalculated. </inglise>
<eesti>Sel juhul makstakse pensioni muutunud suuruses, alates j&auml;rgneva kuu esimesest kuup&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case, the pension shall be paid in the altered amount as of the first day of the following month. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Prokur&ouml;ri invaliidsuspensioni see osa, mis &uuml;letab &uuml;ldise invaliidsuspensioni, makstakse riigieelarvest. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The portion of a prosecutor's disability pension which exceeds the general disability pension shall be paid from the state budget. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. (Kehtetu - 06.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.30.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 53, 315) </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. (Repealed - 06.06.2001 entered into force 30.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 53, 315) </inglise>
<eesti>4. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistuskohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Duties </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametisaladuse hoidmise kohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Obligation of professional secrecy </inglise>
<eesti>Prokur&ouml;r ei tohi avaldada temale seoses teenistus&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisega teatavaks saanud asjaolusid, kui see v&otilde;ib kahjustada &otilde;igusem&otilde;istmist. </eesti>
<inglise>A prosecutor shall not disclose information which becomes known to him or her in connection with the performance of his or her duties if this may prejudice the administration of justice. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametisaladuse hoidmise kohustus on t&auml;htajatu. </eesti>
<inglise>The obligation of professional secrecy has an unspecified term. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhendamiskohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Duty to supervise </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maa- ja linnaprokur&ouml;r on kohustatud maakonna v&otilde;i linna vanemprokur&ouml;ri korraldusel juhendama &otilde;ppeteenistuses v&otilde;i katseajal olevat abiprokur&ouml;ri v&otilde;i praktikanti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) County and city prosecutors are required to supervise assistant prosecutors and trainees during their clerkships and probationary periods on the orders of senior county or city prosecutors. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maa- ja linnaprokur&ouml;r ei ole kohustatud juhendama &uuml;heaegselt rohkem kui &uuml;hte abiprokur&ouml;ri v&otilde;i praktikanti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) No county or city prosecutor shall be required to supervise more than one assistant prosecutor or trainee at a time. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
<eesti>Prokur&ouml;ri teenistuspiirangud </eesti>
<inglise>Restrictions on service of prosecutors </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Prokur&ouml;r ei v&otilde;i v&auml;ljaspool teenistuskohustusi t&ouml;&ouml;tada mujal kui &otilde;ppe- v&otilde;i teadust&ouml;&ouml;l. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Prosecutors shall not be employed elsewhere outside of their professional duties, except for teaching or research. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Prokur&ouml;r ei v&otilde;i olla &auml;ri&uuml;hingu asutaja, juhtimis&otilde;iguslik osanik, juhatuse v&otilde;i n&otilde;ukogu liige ega v&auml;lismaa &auml;ri&uuml;hingu filiaali juhataja, samuti erakonna liige. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A prosecutor shall not be a founder, managing partner, member of the management board or supervisory board of a commercial undertaking, director of a branch of a foreign commercial undertaking, or a member of a political party. </inglise>
<eesti>5. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarvastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Disciplinary Liability </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 31. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 31. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarkaristused </eesti>
<inglise>Disciplinary penalties </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teo eest v&otilde;ib prokur&ouml;rile m&auml;&auml;rata distsiplinaarkaristuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A disciplinary penalty may be imposed on a prosecutor for a disciplinary offence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Distsiplinaarkaristused on: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Disciplinary penalties are: </inglise>
<eesti>1) noomitus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a reprimand; </inglise>
<eesti>2) rahatrahv kuni &uuml;he kuu palga ulatuses; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a fine of up to one month's salary; </inglise>
<eesti>3) palga v&auml;hendamine; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a reduction of salary; </inglise>
<eesti>4) teenistusest vabastamine. </eesti>
<inglise>4) release from service. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 32. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 32. </inglise>
<eesti>Palga v&auml;hendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Reduction of salary </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarkaristusena v&otilde;ib prokur&ouml;ri palka v&auml;hendada mitte rohkem kui veerandi v&otilde;rra ja mitte kauemaks kui &uuml;heks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>As a disciplinary punishment, a prosecutor's salary may be reduced by not more than one quarter and for not longer than one year. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 33. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 33. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarkomisjon </eesti>
<inglise>Disciplinary committee </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Prokur&ouml;ri distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;tegu arutab prokur&ouml;ride distsiplinaarkomisjon. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The prosecutors' disciplinary committee shall consider disciplinary offences committed by prosecutors. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Distsiplinaarkomisjoni koosseisu kuuluvad &uuml;ks riigiprokur&ouml;r, kolm maa- v&otilde;i linnaprokuratuuri prokur&ouml;ri ja &uuml;ks kohtunike esinduskogu valitud kohtunik. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The disciplinary committee shall be comprised of one public prosecutor, a total of three prosecutors from county and city prosecutor's offices, and one judge elected by the representative body of judges. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarkomisjon valitakse kolmeks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>The disciplinary committee shall be elected for three years. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Distsiplinaarkomisjoni esimehe ja tema asendajad valib distsiplinaarkomisjon oma prokur&ouml;ridest liikmete hulgast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The disciplinary committee shall elect the chairman of the disciplinary committee and his or her substitutes from among its members who are prosecutors. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Distsiplinaarkomisjoni t&ouml;&ouml;korra kinnitab justiitsminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Minister of Justice shall approve the procedures of the disciplinary committee. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarkaristuse m&auml;&auml;ramise &otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Right to impose disciplinary penalties </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Distsiplinaarkaristuse m&auml;&auml;ramise &otilde;igus on justiitsministril distsiplinaarkomisjoni ettepanekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Minister of Justice has the right to impose disciplinary penalties on the proposal of the disciplinary committee. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigi peaprokur&ouml;ri teenistusest vabastamise distsiplinaarkaristusena otsustab Vabariigi Valitsus justiitsministri ettepanekul &uuml;he kuu jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Government of the Republic shall decide the release of the Chief Public Prosecutor from service as a disciplinary punishment on the proposal of the Minister of Justice within one month. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarmenetluse algatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Initiation of disciplinary proceedings </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Distsiplinaarmenetluse v&otilde;ib algatada: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Disciplinary proceedings may be initiated by: </inglise>
<eesti>1) justiitsminister v&otilde;i riigi peaprokur&ouml;r k&otilde;igi prokur&ouml;ride suhtes; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the Minister of Justice or the Chief Public Prosecutor against all prosecutors; </inglise>
<eesti>2) maakonna ja linna vanemprokur&ouml;r temale alluvate prokur&ouml;ride suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise>2) a senior county or city prosecutor against prosecutors subordinate to him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Distsiplinaarmenetlus algatatakse k&auml;skkirjaga, mis tehakse viivituseta teatavaks prokur&ouml;rile, kelle suhtes distsiplinaarmenetlus algatati. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A disciplinary proceeding shall be initiated by a directive that shall be promptly communicated to the prosecutor against whom the disciplinary proceeding is initiated. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Distsiplinaarmenetluse algataja v&otilde;ib distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teo kohta koguda t&otilde;endeid ja n&otilde;uda seletusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A person who initiates a disciplinary proceeding may gather evidence and demand explanations concerning the disciplinary offence. </inglise>
<eesti>Seletuse n&otilde;udmine prokur&ouml;rilt, kelle suhtes distsiplinaarmenetlus algatati, on kohustuslik. </eesti>
<inglise>It is compulsory to demand explanations from the prosecutor against whom a disciplinary proceeding is initiated. </inglise>
<eesti>T&otilde;endite kogumise ja seletuste n&otilde;udmise v&otilde;ib justiitsminister teha &uuml;lesandeks riigi peaprokur&ouml;rile, riigi peaprokur&ouml;r v&otilde;i maakonna v&otilde;i linna vanemprokur&ouml;r aga temale vahetult alluvale prokur&ouml;rile. </eesti>
<inglise>The Minister of Justice may assign the task of gathering evidence and demanding explanations to the Chief Public Prosecutor; the Chief Public Prosecutor or a senior county or city prosecutor may assign such task to the prosecutor directly subordinate to him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>Seda &uuml;lesannet ei saa panna prokur&ouml;rile, kes on distsiplinaarkomisjoni liige. </eesti>
<inglise>The task cannot be assigned to a prosecutor who is a member of the disciplinary committee. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Distsiplinaarmenetluse algataja v&otilde;ib distsiplinaarmenetluse ajaks k&otilde;rvaldada prokur&ouml;ri ametist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A person who initiates a disciplinary proceeding may suspend the prosecutor for the time of the disciplinary proceeding. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametist k&otilde;rvaldamise aja eest s&auml;ilitatakse prokur&ouml;rile palk koos lisatasudega. </eesti>
<inglise>During the suspension, the prosecutor shall continue to receive his or her salary together with additional remuneration. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kogutud t&otilde;endite alusel esitab distsiplinaarmenetluse algataja distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;distuse v&otilde;i l&otilde;petab distsiplinaarmenetluse. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) On the basis of gathered evidence, the person who initiated a disciplinary proceeding shall bring a disciplinary charge or terminate the disciplinary proceeding. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 36. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 36. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;distus </eesti>
<inglise>Disciplinary charge </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;distus on kirjalik dokument, milles m&auml;rgitakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A disciplinary charge is a written document, which shall set out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) s&uuml;&uuml;distatava ees- ja perekonnanimi ning ametikoht; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the given name, surname and title of the accused; </inglise>
<eesti>2) s&uuml;&uuml;teo kirjeldus ja toimepanemise aeg; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the description and time of commission of the offence; </inglise>
<eesti>3) s&uuml;&uuml;teo toimepanemist kinnitavad t&otilde;endid; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the evidence proving commission of the offence; </inglise>
<eesti>4) s&uuml;&uuml;distuse esitaja, s&uuml;&uuml;distuse koostamise aeg ja koht. </eesti>
<inglise>4) the person who brings the charge, the date and place of preparation of the charge. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;distust ei v&otilde;i esitada ja distsiplinaarmenetlus tuleb l&otilde;petada, kui distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teo toimepanemisest on m&ouml;&ouml;dunud enam kui &uuml;ks aasta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A disciplinary charge shall not be brought and a disciplinary proceeding shall be terminated if more than one year has passed from the commission of the disciplinary offence. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 37. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 37. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarkomisjoni istungi ettevalmistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Preparation for session of disciplinary committee </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Distsiplinaarkomisjoni istungi aja ja koha m&auml;&auml;rab kindlaks distsiplinaarkomisjoni esimees. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The chairman of the disciplinary committee shall determine the time and place of sessions of the disciplinary committee. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Istungile kutsutakse distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;distuse esitaja ning prokur&ouml;r, kelle distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;tegu arutatakse. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The person who brings a disciplinary charge and the prosecutor whose disciplinary offence is considered shall be invited to the session. </inglise>
<eesti>Abiprokur&ouml;ri suhtes algatatud distsiplinaarmenetluses kutsutakse distsiplinaarkomisjoni istungile ka abiprokur&ouml;ri juhendav prokur&ouml;r. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of a disciplinary proceeding initiated against an assistant prosecutor, his or her supervising prosecutor shall also be invited to the session of the disciplinary committee. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 38. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 38. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;distuse materjalidega tutvumise &otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Right to examine disciplinary charge materials </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Prokur&ouml;rile, kelle vastu distsiplinaarmenetlus on algatatud, antakse distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;distus k&auml;tte v&auml;hemalt kolm p&auml;eva enne distsiplinaarkomisjoni istungit. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A disciplinary charge shall be given to the prosecutor against whom a disciplinary proceeding is initiated at least three days before the session of the disciplinary committee is held. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Prokur&ouml;ril, kellele esitati distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;distus, on &otilde;igus tutvuda distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;distuse materjalidega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A prosecutor against whom a disciplinary charge is brought has the right to examine the materials of the disciplinary charge. </inglise>
<eesti>Abiprokur&ouml;ri distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;distuse materjalidega v&otilde;ib tutvuda ka teda juhendav prokur&ouml;r. </eesti>
<inglise>The materials of a disciplinary charge brought against an assistant prosecutor may also be examined by his or her supervising prosecutor. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 39. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 39. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarkomisjoni istung </eesti>
<inglise>Session of disciplinary committee </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;tegu arutab distsiplinaarkomisjon kinnisel istungil. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The disciplinary committee shall consider a disciplinary offence in a closed session. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Distsiplinaarkomisjon on otsustusv&otilde;imeline, kui istungist v&otilde;tab osa v&auml;hemalt kolm distsiplinaarkomisjoni liiget, sealhulgas esimees. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The disciplinary committee has a quorum if at least three members of the disciplinary committee, including the chairman, participate in the session. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Distsiplinaarkomisjoni istungit juhatab distsiplinaarkomisjoni esimees. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The chairman of the disciplinary committee shall chair sessions of the disciplinary committee. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Distsiplinaarkomisjoni liikmena ei saa isik osaleda temale esitatud distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;distuse arutamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A member of the disciplinary committee cannot participate in the consideration of the disciplinary charge brought against him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 40. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 40. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarkomisjoni otsus </eesti>
<inglise>Decision of disciplinary committee </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Distsiplinaarkomisjoni otsusega tehakse justiitsministrile ettepanek m&auml;&auml;rata distsiplinaarkaristus v&otilde;i j&auml;tta distsiplinaarkaristus m&auml;&auml;ramata v&otilde;i l&otilde;petatakse distsiplinaarmenetlus, kui puudub distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;tegu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) By a decision of the disciplinary committee, a proposal to impose or not to impose a disciplinary penalty shall be made to the Minister of Justice, or the disciplinary proceeding shall be terminated if there was no disciplinary offence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui on vaja koguda lisat&otilde;endeid, l&uuml;kkab distsiplinaarkomisjon distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teo arutamise edasi, m&auml;&auml;rab kindlaks j&auml;rgmise istungi aja ja koha ning teeb lisat&otilde;endite kogumise &uuml;lesandeks &uuml;hele distsiplinaarkomisjoni liikmele v&otilde;i distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;distuse esitajale. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If it is necessary to gather supplementary evidence, the disciplinary committee shall defer the consideration of the disciplinary offence, determine the time and place of the next session and assign the task of gathering supplementary evidence to one member of the disciplinary committee or the person who brought the disciplinary charge. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Distsiplinaarkomisjon teeb otsuse istungist osav&otilde;tvate distsiplinaarkomisjoni liikmete lihth&auml;&auml;lteenamusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The disciplinary committee shall make a decision by a simple majority of the members of the disciplinary committee participating in the session. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui h&auml;&auml;led jagunevad v&otilde;rdselt, otsustab distsiplinaarkomisjoni esimehe h&auml;&auml;l. </eesti>
<inglise>If the votes are divided equally, the chairman of the disciplinary committee shall cast the deciding vote. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 41. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 41. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarkaristuse m&auml;&auml;ramine </eesti>
<inglise>Imposition of disciplinary penalties </inglise>
<eesti>Justiitsminister otsustab distsiplinaarkaristuse m&auml;&auml;ramise v&otilde;i k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 34 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud ettepaneku tegemise &uuml;he kuu jooksul, arvates distsiplinaarkomisjoni ettepaneku saamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>The Minister of Justice shall decide the imposition of disciplinary punishments or the making of a proposal specified in subsection 34 (2) of this Act, within one month after receipt of a proposal of the disciplinary committee. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 42. (Kehtetu - 11.02.99 j&otilde;ust.24.02.99 - RT I 1999, 18, 303) </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 42. (Repealed - 11.02.99 entered into force 24.02.99 - RT I 1999, 18, 303) </inglise>
<eesti>6. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 6 </inglise>
<eesti>Atesteerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Evaluation </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 43. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 43. </inglise>
<eesti>Prokur&ouml;ride konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon </eesti>
<inglise>Prosecutors' competition and evaluation committee </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Prokur&ouml;ride konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon atesteerib isikuid, kes kandideerivad prokur&ouml;ri ametikohale, kui prokur&ouml;ri ametikoht t&auml;idetakse avaliku konkursi korras, korraldab prokur&ouml;rieksami ning hindab abiprokur&ouml;ri katseaja tulemust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The prosecutors' competition and evaluation committee shall evaluate persons applying for the position of prosecutor if the position is filled by way of a public competition, shall organise prosecutor's examinations and assess the results of the probationary periods of assistant prosecutors. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Prokur&ouml;ride konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni koosseisu kuuluvad riigi peaprokur&ouml;r, &uuml;ks riigiprokur&ouml;r, kaks maa- v&otilde;i linnaprokuratuuri prokur&ouml;ri, &uuml;ks kohtunike esinduskogu valitud kohtunik, Tartu &Uuml;likooli &otilde;igusteaduskonna dekaani m&auml;&auml;ratud &otilde;igusteadlane ja justiitsministri m&auml;&auml;ratud Justiitsministeeriumi ametnik. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The prosecutors' competition and evaluation committee shall be comprised of the Chief Public Prosecutor, one public prosecutor, a total of two prosecutors from county and city prosecutor's offices, one judge elected by the representative body of judges, a jurist designated by the Dean of the Law Faculty of the University of Tartu and an official of the Ministry of Justice designated by the Minister of Justice. </inglise>
<eesti>Konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni liikme, v&auml;lja arvatud riigi peaprokur&ouml;ri ja Justiitsministeeriumi ametniku volitused kestavad kolm aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>The term of authority of a member of the prosecutors' competition and evaluation committee, excluding the Chief Public Prosecutor and an official of the Ministry of Justice, shall be three years. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Prokur&ouml;ride konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni esimees on riigi peaprokur&ouml;r. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Chief Public Prosecutor shall be the chairman of the prosecutors' competition and evaluation committee. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Prokur&ouml;ride konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon on otsustusv&otilde;imeline, kui istungist v&otilde;tab osa v&auml;hemalt viis komisjoni liiget, sealhulgas esimees. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The prosecutors' competition and evaluation committee has a quorum if at least five members of the committee, including the chairman, participate in the session. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Prokur&ouml;ride konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni asjaajamist korraldab Riigiprokuratuur. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The Public Prosecutor's Office shall manage the operations of the prosecutors' competition and evaluation committee. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 44. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 44. </inglise>
<eesti>Atesteerimise n&otilde;uded ja viis </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements and method of evaluation </inglise>
<eesti>Atesteerimisel prokur&ouml;rile esitatavad n&otilde;uded ja atesteerimise viisi kehtestab justiitsminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The Minister of Justice shall establish the evaluation requirements for prosecutors and the method of evaluation. </inglise>
<eesti>7. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 7 </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusest vabastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Release from Service </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 45. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 45. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusest vabastamine omal soovil </eesti>
<inglise>Release from service at own request </inglise>
<eesti>Prokur&ouml;r v&otilde;idakse teenistusest vabastada omal soovil. </eesti>
<inglise>A prosecutor may be released from service at his or her own request. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 46. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 46. </inglise>
<eesti>Abiprokur&ouml;ri teenistusest vabastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Release of assistant prosecutor from service </inglise>
<eesti>Abiprokur&ouml;r vabastatakse teenistusest, kui ta ei soorita prokur&ouml;rieksamit v&otilde;i korduseksamit. </eesti>
<inglise>An assistant prosecutor shall be released from service if he or she fails the prosecutor's examination or re-examination. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 47. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 47. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusest vabastamine vanuse t&otilde;ttu </eesti>
<inglise>Release from service due to age </inglise>
<eesti>Prokur&ouml;ri v&otilde;ib vabastada teenistusest, kui ta on saanud 65-aastaseks. </eesti>
<inglise>A prosecutor may be released from service when he or she attains sixty-five years of age. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 48. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 48. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusest vabastamine pankroti korral </eesti>
<inglise>Release from service due to bankruptcy </inglise>
<eesti>Prokur&ouml;r vabastatakse teenistusest, kui on v&auml;lja kuulutatud tema pankrot. </eesti>
<inglise>A prosecutor shall be released from service if he or she is declared bankrupt. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 49. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 49. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusest vabastamine distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teo eest </eesti>
<inglise>Release from service for disciplinary offence </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teo eest vabastatakse prokur&ouml;r teenistusest k&auml;esoleva seaduse 5. jaos s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>A prosecutor shall be released from service for a disciplinary offence pursuant to the procedure provided for in Division 5 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 50. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 50. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigi peaprokur&ouml;ri ning maakonna ja linna vanemprokur&ouml;ri ametist vabastamine ametiaja l&otilde;ppemise t&otilde;ttu </eesti>
<inglise>Release of Chief Public Prosecutor or senior county or city prosecutor from service due to expiry of term of office </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametiaja l&otilde;ppemisel vabastab justiitsminister riigi peaprokur&ouml;ri v&otilde;i maakonna v&otilde;i linna vanemprokur&ouml;ri ametist ning nimetab: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon the expiry of the term of office of the Chief Public Prosecutor or a senior county or city prosecutor, the Minister of Justice shall release him or her from office and shall appoint: </inglise>
<eesti>1) riigi peaprokur&ouml;ri - riigiprokur&ouml;riks v&otilde;i maakonna v&otilde;i linna vanemprokur&ouml;riks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the Chief Public Prosecutor as a public prosecutor or senior county or city prosecutor; </inglise>
<eesti>2) maakonna ja linna vanemprokur&ouml;ri - teise maakonna v&otilde;i linna vanemprokur&ouml;riks v&otilde;i maa- v&otilde;i linnaprokur&ouml;riks. </eesti>
<inglise>2) a senior county or city prosecutor as a senior county or city prosecutor of another county or city, or as a county or city prosecutor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui riigi peaprokur&ouml;r p&auml;rast ametiaja l&otilde;ppemist seda soovib, nimetatakse ta vaba ametikoha olemasolu korral maa- v&otilde;i linnaprokur&ouml;riks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Chief Public Prosecutor shall be appointed as a county or city prosecutor upon the existence of a vacant position if he or she so requests after the expiry of his or her term of office. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 s&auml;testatud ametisse nimetamine toimub avaliku konkursita. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The appointments to office provided for in subsections (1) and (2) of this section shall be effected without a public competition. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Riigi peaprokur&ouml;ri ning maakonna ja linna vanemprokur&ouml;ri v&otilde;ib uueks ametiajaks ametisse tagasi nimetada. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Chief Public Prosecutor and senior county and city prosecutors may be reappointed to office for a new term of office. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Riigi peaprokur&ouml;ri ning maakonna ja linna vanemprokur&ouml;ri v&otilde;ib k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud ametikohale nimetada v&otilde;i ametisse tagasi nimetada tema kirjaliku n&otilde;usoleku korral. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The Chief Public Prosecutor and senior county and city prosecutors may be appointed to a position provided for in subsection (1) of this section or reappointed to office, with their written consent. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kui riigi peaprokur&ouml;r v&otilde;i maakonna v&otilde;i linna vanemprokur&ouml;r ei ole n&otilde;us k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud ametikohale nimetamisega v&otilde;i kui riigi peaprokur&ouml;r ei soovi enda nimetamist maa- v&otilde;i linnaprokur&ouml;riks v&otilde;i puudub vaba maa- v&otilde;i linnaprokur&ouml;ri ametikoht, vabastatakse ta teenistusest. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) If the Chief Public Prosecutor or a senior county or city prosecutor does not consent to be appointed to a position provided for in subsection (1) of this section, if the Chief Public Prosecutor does not wish to be appointed as a county or city prosecutor, or if there is no vacant position of county or city prosecutor, he or she shall be released from service. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 51. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 51. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusest vabastamise erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Exceptions to release from service </inglise>
<eesti>Prokur&ouml;rile ei kohaldata avaliku teenistuse seaduse paragrahv 117 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 4 ja 6 s&auml;testatud teenistusest vabastamise aluseid. </eesti>
<inglise>The bases for release from service provided for in clauses 117 (1) 4) and 6) of the Public Service Act do not apply to prosecutors. </inglise>
<eesti>8. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 8 </inglise>
<eesti>Prokur&ouml;ri kaasamine haldus&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisele </eesti>
<inglise>Engagement of prosecutors in performance of administrative duties </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 52. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 52. </inglise>
<eesti>Prokur&ouml;ri kaasamine haldus&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisele </eesti>
<inglise>Engagement of prosecutors in performance of administrative duties </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kuulanud &auml;ra riigi peaprokur&ouml;ri arvamuse, v&otilde;ib justiitsminister nimetada prokur&ouml;ri tema n&otilde;usolekul Justiitsministeeriumi v&otilde;i Riigiprokuratuuri koosseisus etten&auml;htud ametikohale prokuratuuride haldamise &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) After hearing the opinion of the Chief Public Prosecutor, the Minister of Justice may appoint a prosecutor, with his or her consent, to a position on the staff of the Ministry of Justice or the Public Prosecutor's Office in order to perform the duties of administration of prosecutor's offices. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Prokur&ouml;ri nimetamise korral Justiitsministeeriumi v&otilde;i Riigiprokuratuuri koosseisus etten&auml;htud ametikohale s&auml;ilivad tal prokur&ouml;rile etten&auml;htud ametih&uuml;ved. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon appointing a prosecutor to a position on the staff of the Ministry of Justice or the Public Prosecutor's Office, the prosecutor shall retain the benefits related to office prescribed for prosecutors. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Prokur&ouml;r, kes on k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud alusel t&ouml;&ouml;tanud Justiitsministeeriumis v&otilde;i Riigiprokuratuuris v&auml;hemalt kaks aastat, nimetatakse avaliku konkursita tema soovil tagasi prokur&ouml;riks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A prosecutor who has been employed in the Ministry of Justice or the Public Prosecutor's Office on the basis specified in subsection (1) of this section for at least two years shall be reappointed as a prosecutor at his or her request without a public competition. </inglise>
<eesti>Sel juhul ei v&otilde;i justiitsminister prokur&ouml;ri vaba ametikoha olemasolu korral keelduda prokur&ouml;ri ametisse tagasi nimetamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case, the Minister of Justice cannot refuse to reappoint the prosecutor upon the existence of a vacant position of prosecutor. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Teenistusaeg Justiitsministeeriumis v&otilde;i Riigiprokuratuuris arvatakse selle ametikoha teenistusaja hulka, kus prokur&ouml;r t&ouml;&ouml;tas enne Justiitsministeeriumi v&otilde;i Riigiprokuratuuri koosseisus etten&auml;htud ametikohale nimetamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The period of service in the Ministry of Justice or the Public Prosecutor's Office shall be included in the period of service in the position in which the prosecutor was employed before appointment to a position on the staff of the Ministry of Justice or the Public Prosecutor's Office. </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Rakenduss&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>Implementing Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 53. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 53. </inglise>
<eesti>Prokur&ouml;ride ametisse nimetamine </eesti>
<inglise>Appointment of prosecutors to office </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Seaduse j&otilde;ustumise ajal ametis olevad prokur&ouml;rid nimetab justiitsminister: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Prosecutors who are in office on the date of entry into force of this Act shall be appointed by the Minister of Justice as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) maa- v&otilde;i linnaprokur&ouml;ri - maakonna v&otilde;i linna vanemprokur&ouml;riks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a county or city prosecutor as a senior county or city prosecutor; </inglise>
<eesti>2) maa- v&otilde;i linnaprokur&ouml;ri aset&auml;itja - maa- v&otilde;i linnaprokur&ouml;riks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a deputy county or city prosecutor as a county or city prosecutor; </inglise>
<eesti>3) maa- v&otilde;i linna abiprokur&ouml;ri - maa- v&otilde;i linnaprokur&ouml;riks, kui tal on k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 15 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud &otilde;igusalane k&otilde;rgharidus; </eesti>
<inglise>3) an assistant county or city prosecutor as a county or city prosecutor if he or she has completed an academic higher education in law specified in subsection 15 (1) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>4) maa- v&otilde;i linna abiprokur&ouml;ri - abiprokur&ouml;riks, kui ta ei vasta k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktis 3 m&auml;rgitud n&otilde;udele; </eesti>
<inglise>4) an assistant county or city prosecutor as an assistant prosecutor if he or she does not meet the requirement specified in clause 3) of this subsection; </inglise>
<eesti>5) prokur&ouml;rikandidaadi - abiprokur&ouml;riks. </eesti>
<inglise>5) a prosecutor-designate as an assistant prosecutor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punkti 4 alusel ametisse nimetatud abiprokur&ouml;rile &otilde;ppeteenistust ja katseaega ei kohaldata. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Assistant prosecutors appointed to office pursuant to clause (1) 4) of this section are not required to undergo a clerkship or probationary period. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punkti 5 alusel ametisse nimetatud abiprokur&ouml;r l&auml;bib &otilde;ppeteenistuse. </eesti>
<inglise>Assistant prosecutors appointed to office pursuant to clause (1) 5) of this section shall undergo a clerkship. </inglise>
<eesti>Prokur&ouml;rikandidaadina t&ouml;&ouml;tamise aeg arvatakse &otilde;ppeteenistuse aja hulka. </eesti>
<inglise>The period of employment as a prosecutor-designate shall be included in the clerkship period. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Riigi peaprokur&ouml;ri nimetab ametisse Vabariigi Valitsus justiitsministri ettepanekul &uuml;he kuu jooksul k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Government of the Republic shall appoint the Chief Public Prosecutor to office on the proposal of the Minister of Justice within one month after the entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Kuni riigi peaprokur&ouml;ri ametisse nimetamiseni t&auml;idab tema &uuml;lesandeid k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumise ajal ametis olev riigiprokur&ouml;r v&otilde;i tema kohuset&auml;itja. </eesti>
<inglise>Until the appointment of the Chief Public Prosecutor to office, his or her duties shall be performed by the public prosecutor or acting public prosecutor who is in office on the date of entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Riigiprokur&ouml;rid nimetab justiitsminister ametisse avaliku konkursi alusel atesteerimiskomisjoni ettepanekul &uuml;he aasta jooksul k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Minister of Justice shall appoint public prosecutors to office on the basis of a public competition on the proposal of the evaluation committee within one year after the entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Kuni riigiprokur&ouml;ride ametisse nimetamiseni t&auml;idavad riigiprokur&ouml;ride &uuml;lesandeid seaduse j&otilde;ustumise ajal Riigiprokuratuuris ametis olevad prokur&ouml;rid. </eesti>
<inglise>Until the appointment of public prosecutors to office, the duties of public prosecutors shall be performed by the prosecutors who are in office in the Public Prosecutor's Office on the date of entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumise ajal ametis olevat riigiprokur&ouml;ri aset&auml;itjat v&otilde;i Riigiprokuratuuri prokur&ouml;ri ei nimetata riigi peaprokur&ouml;riks v&otilde;i riigiprokur&ouml;riks, viib justiitsminister prokur&ouml;ri tema n&otilde;usolekul avaliku konkursita &uuml;le prokur&ouml;ri vabale ametikohale maa- v&otilde;i linnaprokuratuuris. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If a deputy public prosecutor or a prosecutor of the Public Prosecutor's Office who is in office on the date of entry into force of this Act is not appointed as the Chief Public Prosecutor or a public prosecutor, the Minister of Justice shall transfer the prosecutor, with his or her consent, to a vacant position of prosecutor in a county or city prosecutor's office without a public competition. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui prokur&ouml;r sellega ei n&otilde;ustu, vabastab justiitsminister ta teenistusest koondamise t&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise>If a prosecutor does not give his or her consent, the Minister of Justice shall release him or her from service due to redundancy. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) K&otilde;ik maakonna ja linna vanemprokur&ouml;rid nimetab k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 17 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud t&auml;htajaks ametisse justiitsminister &uuml;he aasta jooksul k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisest prokur&ouml;ride konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni ettepanekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The Minister of Justice shall appoint all the senior county and city prosecutors to office on the proposal of the prosecutors' competition and evaluation committee for the term provided for in subsection 17 (2) of this Act, within one year after the entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punkti 1 alusel ametisse nimetatud maakonna v&otilde;i linna vanemprokur&ouml;ri ei nimetata maakonna v&otilde;i linna vanemprokur&ouml;riks, viib justiitsminister prokur&ouml;ri tema n&otilde;usolekul avaliku konkursita &uuml;le prokur&ouml;ri vabale ametikohale maa- v&otilde;i linnaprokuratuuris. </eesti>
<inglise>If a current senior county or city prosecutor who was appointed to office pursuant to clause (1) 1) of this section is not appointed as a senior county or city prosecutor, the Minister of Justice shall transfer the prosecutor, with his or her consent, to a vacant position of prosecutor in a county or city prosecutor's office without a public competition. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui prokur&ouml;r sellega ei n&otilde;ustu, vabastab justiitsminister ta teenistusest koondamise t&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise>If a prosecutor does not give his or her consent, the Minister of Justice shall release him or her from service due to redundancy. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.02.99 j&otilde;ust.24.02.99 - RT I 1999, 18, 303) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.02.99 entered into force 24.02.99 - RT I 1999, 18, 303) </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Prokur&ouml;ri vabadele ametikohtadele maa- ja linnaprokuratuuris nimetab justiitsminister prokur&ouml;rid avaliku konkursi alusel atesteerimiskomisjoni ettepanekul &uuml;he aasta jooksul k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The Minister of Justice shall appoint prosecutors to the vacant positions of prosecutor in county and city prosecutor's offices on the basis of a public competition and on the proposal of the evaluation committee, within one year after the entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) K&auml;esolevas paragrahvis s&auml;testatud ametisse nimetamisele ei kohaldata k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 15 l&otilde;ikeid 3-5. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) Subsections 15 (3) -(5) of this Act do not apply to the appointments to office provided for in this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi alusel ametisse nimetatud prokur&ouml;ri teenistusaeg ametisse nimetamisele eelneval prokur&ouml;ri ametikohal arvatakse uue ametikoha teenistusaja hulka k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 15 t&auml;henduses. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) The period of service of a prosecutor in a position of prosecutor prior to appointment to office pursuant to this section shall be included in his or her period of service in the new position within the meaning of &sect; 15 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 54. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 54. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiprokuratuuri prokur&ouml;ri ametipalk </eesti>
<inglise>Prosecutor's salary in Public Prosecutor's Office </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 53 l&otilde;ike 3 teises lauses m&auml;rgitud riigiprokur&ouml;r v&otilde;i tema kohuset&auml;itja saab riigi peaprokur&ouml;ri &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmise ajal riigi peaprokur&ouml;ri ametipalka. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A public prosecutor or acting public prosecutor specified in the second sentence of subsection 53 (3) of this Act shall receive the salary of the Chief Public Prosecutor during the time he or she performs the duties of the Chief Public Prosecutor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 53 l&otilde;ike 4 teises lauses m&auml;rgitud riigiprokur&ouml;ri aset&auml;itja saab riigiprokur&ouml;ri &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmise ajal Riigiprokuratuuri osakonda juhtiva prokur&ouml;ri ametipalka. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A deputy public prosecutor specified in the second sentence of subsection 53 (4) of this Act shall receive the salary of a prosecutor who directs a department of the Public Prosecutor's Office during the time he or she performs the duties of a public prosecutor. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 53 l&otilde;ike 4 teises lauses m&auml;rgitud Riigiprokuratuuri prokur&ouml;ri ametipalk riigiprokur&ouml;ri &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmise ajal on k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 22 l&otilde;ikes 1 m&auml;rgitud palgam&auml;&auml;ra ja 1,15 korrutis. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The salary of a prosecutor of the Public Prosecutor's Office specified in the second sentence of subsection 53 (4) of this Act during the time he or she performs the duties of a public prosecutor shall be the salary rate specified in subsection 22 (1) multiplied by 1.15. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 55. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 55. </inglise>
<eesti>Esimese prokur&ouml;ride &uuml;ldkogu kokkukutsumine </eesti>
<inglise>Convention of first Prosecutors' Assembly </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Esimese prokur&ouml;ride &uuml;ldkogu kutsub kokku riigi peaprokur&ouml;r &uuml;he kuu jooksul ametisse nimetamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Chief Public Prosecutor shall convene the first Prosecutors' Assembly within one month after appointment to office. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Esimene prokur&ouml;ride &uuml;ldkogu valib prokur&ouml;ridest konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni ning distsiplinaarkomisjoni liikmed. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The first Prosecutors' Assembly shall elect the members of the prosecutors' competition and evaluation committee and of the disciplinary committee from among the prosecutors. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kuni kohtunike esinduskogu ei ole distsiplinaarkomisjoni ega prokur&ouml;ride konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni kohtunikust liiget valinud, teeb seda Kohtunike &Uuml;hingu juhatus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) As long as the representative body of judges has not elected a member of the prosecutors' competition and evaluation committee or the disciplinary committee from among the judges, the Board of the Association of Judges shall do so. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Distsiplinaarkomisjoni ning prokur&ouml;ride konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni riigiprokur&ouml;rist liige valitakse p&auml;rast riigiprokur&ouml;ride ametisse nimetamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The member of the disciplinary committee and the member of the prosecutors' competition and evaluation committee who are public prosecutors shall be elected after the appointment of public prosecutors to office. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 56. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 56. </inglise>
<eesti>Prokur&ouml;ride atesteerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Evaluation of prosecutors </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&otilde;ik prokur&ouml;rid, v&auml;lja arvatud riigi peaprokur&ouml;r, kuuluvad atesteerimisele viie aasta jooksul, arvates k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) All prosecutors, except the Chief Public Prosecutor, are subject to evaluation within five years after the entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Atesteerimise k&auml;igus hinnatakse prokur&ouml;ri teadmisi ja kutseoskusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the course of evaluation, the knowledge and professional skills of prosecutors shall be assessed. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Atesteerimise n&otilde;uded, viisi ja aja m&auml;&auml;rab justiitsminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Minister of Justice shall determine the requirements for and the method and time of evaluation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 57. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 57. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 15 l&otilde;ike 1 kohaldamise erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Specifications for application of subsection 15 (1) of this Act </inglise>
<eesti>Isiku, kes on saanud akadeemilise k&otilde;rghariduse &otilde;igusteaduses era&otilde;iguslikus &uuml;likoolis, v&otilde;ib nimetada prokur&ouml;riks, kui ta on omandanud k&otilde;rghariduse akrediteeritud &otilde;ppekava alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>Persons who have completed an academic higher education in law in a university in private law may be appointed as prosecutors if they have completed such higher education on the basis of an accredited curriculum. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 58. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 58. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 22 kohaldamise erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Specifications for application of &sect; 22 of this Act </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisest k&uuml;mne aasta jooksul v&otilde;ib Vabariigi Valitsus m&otilde;nes piirkonnas t&ouml;&ouml;tavate prokur&ouml;ride ametipalka suurendada kuni neljandiku v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise>Within ten years after the entry into force of this Act, the Government of the Republic may increase the salary of prosecutors employed in some regions by up to one quarter. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 59. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 59. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvide 25 ja 26 kohaldamise erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Specifications for application of &sect;&sect; 25 and 26 of this Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvisid 25 ja 26 kohaldatakse isikute suhtes, kes t&ouml;&ouml;tavad prokur&ouml;rina seaduse j&otilde;ustumise ajal v&otilde;i p&auml;rast seaduse j&otilde;ustumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Sections 25 and 26 of this Act apply in respect of persons who are employed as prosecutors on the date of entry into force of this Act or after the entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Prokur&ouml;rina t&ouml;&ouml;tamise aja hulka arvatakse ka prokuratuuri uurijana t&ouml;&ouml;tamise aeg. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The period of employment as a preliminary investigator of a Prosecutor's Office shall be included in the period of employment as a prosecutor. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 59 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 59 (1). </inglise>
